Uses of Package
cps.api.action

  • Packages that use cps.api.action 
    Package Description
    cps.api.action  
    cps.api.request  
    cps.server  
    cps.server.controllers  
  • Classes in cps.api.action used by cps.api.action 
    Class and Description
    LotAction
    Base class for various service actions that deal with parking lots.
    ParkingCellToggleAction
    Base class for actions that toggle boolean flags in parking cells.
    RequestReportAction
    Base Class for actions that request statistical reports.
    ServiceAction
    Base class for all service actions - actions that can be performed by employees of the system and the global manager.
  • Classes in cps.api.action used by cps.api.request 
    Class and Description
    GetCurrentPerformanceAction
    Is sent by the client application when the Global Manager wants to see current performance statistics.
    GetPeriodicReportAction
    Is sent by the client application when the Global Manager wants to see periodic activity statistics.
    GetQuarterlyReportAction
    Is sent by the client application when the Global Manager wants to receive a quarterly statistical report.
    GetWeeklyReportAction
    Is sent by the client application when the Global Manager wants to receive a weekly statistical report.
    InitLotAction
    Is sent by the client application when a local employee wants to initialize a parking lot.
    ListComplaintsAction
    Is sent by the client application when a customer service employee wants to see a list of customer complaints.
    ParkingCellSetDisabledAction
    Is sent by the client application when a local employee wants to mark a parking cell as disabled.
    ParkingCellSetReservedAction
    Is sent by the client application when a local employee wants to mark a parking cell as reserved.
    RefundAction
    Is sent by the client application when a customer service employee wants to refund a customer that filed a complaint.
    RejectComplaintAction
    Is sent by the client application when a customer service employee wants to reject a customer's complaint.
    RequestLotStateAction
    Is sent by the client application when the application needs to have access to the internal state of a parking lot.
    ServiceLoginAction
    Is sent by the client application when an employee or the global manager want to login via the service interface.
    ServiceLogoutAction
    Is sent by the client application when a user wants to log out via the service interface (the interface for employees and the global manager).
    SetFullLotAction
    Is sent by the client application when a local employee wants to mark a parking lot as full and/or to set a list of alternative parking lots where customers will be redirected in case the current parking lot is full.
    UpdatePricesAction
    Is sent by the client application when a local manager wants to update the prices in a parking lot.
